== Legacy ==
Keith was mourned by many people, including his family, strangely. Several musicians like Henry Skelton and Brian Zhang made tribute songs/albums to Keith. In 1994, 11 years after Keith's death, a compilation album was put together. This album's sales exceeded ''Old Eagles Still Scream''. 

== Rumored children ==
{{Infobox_album|title=White Buffalo|artist=Keith Gatwick|released=July 12th, 1979|recorded=August 1978-February 1979|length=47:54|label=Sandpiper Studios|producer=Brian Zhang}}
While Keith and Richardson never had children while they were married, Richardson mothered another child with a different man after the divorce. She also had a 2nd child in 1983 to which the father is unknown. It is rumored that Gatwick and Richardson got back together for a short period, and Gatwick got her pregnant. This was never confirmed.
